                <h3 class="features-title">James Riley</h3>
                <p>As a longtime software developer, I bring a wealth of knowledge about Ruby, Python, PHP, MySQL, PostgreSQL and other stack components to vNucleus, along with an extensive Linux systems administration career.</p>
                <p>Having worked as a systems administrator for a company with 80,000 devices on its network and over 2000 servers, I started doing small scale virtualization back in 2005, and by 2010 had taken a role in a virtualization deployment that took approximately 800 physical servers and consolidated them onto fewer than 20 hosts. After that role I moved on to take a DevOps role at a leading human resources management software development company, where I helped manage an OpenStack cloud with over 8TB of RAM.</p>
                <p>My experience in secure, high performance virtualization environments allows me to fine tune our servers to meet the performance demands and security expectations of every client.</p>
