                <h3 class="features-title">Taylor Burnham</h3>
                <p>My first adventure in systems administration was hosting a dedicated Counter Strike 1.6 server when I was in high school that was funded purely from donations. This was only the beginning of my interest in server and network administration.</p>
                <p>My work experience includes a 24/7/365 department of a telecommunications vendor with government mandated uptime requirements, being the sole engineering escalation point for a life sciences software company, and nowadays maintaining mission critical clinical applications for one of the largest contract research organizations in the world.</p>
                <p>In my spare time I enjoy playing video games, hiking, and listening to a lot of <a href="http://www.last.fm/user/TunedDownGuitar">music</a>.</p>
